title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that finds all the purchases in the household appliances file for purchases made in october 2025. It should only include purchases for organisation which have more than 10 departments, also return the creditor name of these purchases as well as the price and the purchase line. Output in a textfile.

operations.table: (SELECT organisation_id, department_id, creditor_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_price, invoice_line_descr FROM factpurchases) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val date = r.getField(3).toString; date.compareTo("2025-10-01") >= 0 && date.compareTo("2025-10-31") <= 0 }

(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val deptId = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val credId = r.getField(2).asInstanceOf[Int]; val price = r.getField(4).asInstanceOf[Double]; val line = r.getField(5).toString; (orgId, deptId, credId, price, line) }

operations.table: (SELECT organisation_id, department_id FROM department) as X
(SELECT creditor_id, name FROM creditor) as X

operations.udf: (t: ((Int, Int, Int, Double, String), (Int, String))) => { val credName = t._2._2; val price = t._1._4; val line = t._1._5; (credName, price, line) }

log.thoughts: Plan filters purchases in October 2025, keeps only organisations with more than 10 departments, joins to fetch creditor names, and outputs creditor, price and line to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, department_id, creditor_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_price, invoice_line_descr FROM (SELECT organisation_id, department_id, creditor_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_price, invoice_line_descr FROM factpurchases) as X) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val date = r.getField(3).toString; date.compareTo("2025-10-01") >= 0 && date.compareTo("2025-10-31") <= 0 }

(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val orgId = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val deptId = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val credId = r.getField(2).asInstanceOf[Int]; val price = r.getField(4).asInstanceOf[Double]; val line = r.getField(5).toString; (orgId, deptId, credId, price, line) }

data.table: (SELECT organisation_id, department_id FROM (SELECT organisation_id, department_id FROM department) as X) as X
(SELECT creditor_id, name FROM (SELECT creditor_id, name FROM creditor) as X) as X

data.udf: (t: ((Int, Int, Int, Double, String), (Int, String))) => { val credName = t._2._2; val price = t._1._4; val line = t._1._5; (credName, price, line) }
